// auto-continue cold-worktree-spawn focus fix (2026-06-03; hardened 2026-06-05 / dual-brain codex+Gemini).
//
// A fresh per-session worktree window has TWO Claude inputs in play:
//   - the handoff URI (.../open?prompt=) opens the prompt in the EDITOR-area Claude panel
//     (claude-vscode.primaryEditor.open → viewType claudeVSCodePanel), AND
//   - the window may ALSO restore a visible SIDEBAR Claude view from the previous window's layout.
//
// The extension's `claude-vscode.focus` only reveals/focuses the EDITOR Claude when NO sidebar Claude
// webview is visible:  `if(!hasVisibleWebview()) await editor.openLast(); ...`  — and `hasVisibleWebview()`
// counts ONLY the registered SIDEBAR views (claudeVSCodeSidebar / -Secondary), NOT the editor panel.
// So when a sidebar Claude IS visible, the focus command SKIPS editor.openLast and the keyboard focus
// stays on the EMPTY sidebar Claude → the synthetic Enter submits nothing → the worktree transcript
// never grows → auto-continue.sh ABORTs ("3 Enter attempts, no transcript growth"; observed 2026-06-05
// 03:09 on erp-reset-phase2-execute; the evening cold spawns succeeded because their sidebar was the
// Explorer, not Claude). Root cause confirmed by decompiling anthropic.claude-code 2.1.162.
//
// Fix: bind the chord auto-continue.sh sends on COLD windows (ctrl+alt+cmd+0, HANDOFF_FOCUS_KEY=0) to
// `runCommands` that FIRST closes both sidebars (primary + secondary) so no sidebar Claude is visible
// (hasVisibleWebview()=false), THEN runs claude-vscode.focus — which now deterministically routes to
// editor.openLast and focuses the editor Claude holding the prompt. Paired with
// `"claudeCode.preferredLocation": "panel"` injected into the worktree .handoff.code-workspace so
// editor.openLast targets the editor (not the sidebar) even if the global config drifted.
//
// WARM (main-repo) spawns do NOT send this chord (auto-continue do_focus=0), so their windows are
// untouched — closing sidebars only ever happens on freshly-spawned cold worktree windows.
//
// Merge this object into ~/Library/Application Support/Code/User/keybindings.json (the array).
[
  {
    "key": "ctrl+alt+cmd+0",
    "command": "runCommands",
    "args": {
      "commands": [
        "workbench.action.closeSidebar",
        "workbench.action.closeAuxiliaryBar",
        "claude-vscode.focus"
      ]
    }
  }
]
